EC2 Instance → Network & Security → Security Groups
│
├── Default Security Group
│     (Auto-created by AWS for the VPC — allows internal communication
│      between resources within the same security group)
│
└── launch-wizard-1
      (Auto-created by AWS when you launched your EC2 instance via the wizard)
      │
      └── Inbound Rules
            (Control incoming traffic allowed to reach your EC2 instance)
            (Part of a Security Group — acts as a virtual firewall)
            │
            ├── 1. HTTP  | TCP | Port 80  | Source: 0.0.0.0/0
            │         → Allows web traffic from ANY IP address
            │
            └── 2. SSH   | TCP | Port 22  | Source: 0.0.0.0/0
                      → Allows remote terminal/command line access from ANY IP address
                        If Web is not working then we need to take a look into this port

Type	      Port	  Use Case
SSH	        22	    Remote server access
HTTP	      80	    Web traffic
HTTPS	      443	    Secure web traffic
MS SQL	    1433	  SQL Server database access
Custom TCP	Any	    Application-specific ports
